"""
D3AS Pattern Lab — Python Edition (v2)
=======================================
Implements all 12 SEAD/DEAD bait search algorithms, updated to match
the new simulation.py architecture:

  - Drones fly by ANGLE (set at init), not by target-seeking each tick
  - Bait speed: 3.33 mi/tick (200 mph), Recv speed: 5.0 mi/tick
  - Radars cycle ON for 5 ticks every 30-tick window (random power_offset)
  - SAMs are paired to radars, have finite missiles (2 each), 90% hit rate
  - Launchers placed within 10 miles of their paired radar
  - Any drone (bait or recv) can destroy radar/launcher on contact and dies
  - Gas targets: drone survives on collection
  - visited_coords prevents overlap between drones

Each algorithm sets the bait drone angles at init. Recv drone angles
are set by the standard fan-out. Algorithms may also override recv angles
for coordinated patterns.

Scoring:
  Radar kill:    +4 pts
  Launcher kill: +3 pts
  Gas collect:   +1 pt
  Max possible:  6x4 + 6x3 + 4x1 = 46 pts

Usage:
    python d3as_patterns.py                     # all 12 algorithms, 50 trials
    python d3as_patterns.py --trials 200
    python d3as_patterns.py --bait 15 --recv 8
    python d3as_patterns.py --algo 1 5 11       # specific algorithms
    python d3as_patterns.py --preview 6         # animated terminal preview
    python d3as_patterns.py --list              # list all algorithms
"""

